{"articleHTML":"<div class=\"articleContent articleContent--introduction\" data-route-mode=\"bound\"><p><strong>Distance</strong>: 44.7 miles<br>\n<strong>Elevation</strong>: <span style=\"color:green\">+7438</span> <span style=\"color:#ca4747\">-7847</span> feet<br>\n<strong>Running time</strong>: 8 hours 37 minutes<br>\n<strong>Transit time</strong>: 1 hour 50 minutes<br>\n<strong>Transit fare</strong>: $4.90 + bus transfer + $5.40 = $10.30<br>\n<a href=\"https://www.gaiagps.com/public/w6tnBZEZzYqkgbiSJVRfrPGV/\">View on GaiaGPS →</a></p><p>I've wanted to run the Ohlone Trail through <a href=\"https://www.ebparks.org/parks/ohlone\">Ohlone Wilderness Regional Preserve</a> for years now. Shortly after arriving in the Bay Area, we hiked <a href=\"https://www.alltrails.com/trail/us/california/murietta-falls-trail\">twelve miles out and back</a> from Lake Del Valle to Murietta Falls. It was idyllic and intimidating to run through beautiful meadows knowing you've barely even scratched the surface of the trail system.</p><p>The Ohlone Trail has remained on my to-do list for a number of reasons though. First is the nature of the trail itself. The Ohlone Trail starts at <a href=\"https://www.ebparks.org/parks/del-valle\">Lake Del Valle</a> and spans about 27 miles, passing through <a href=\"https://www.ebparks.org/parks/ohlone\">Ohlone Wilderness Regional Preserve</a> and <a href=\"https://www.ebparks.org/parks/sunol\">Sunol Wilderness Regional Preserve</a> before traversing <a href=\"https://www.ebparks.org/parks/mission-peak\">Misson Peak Regional Preserve</a> and ending in Fremont. The trail is <em>very</em> committing, with essentially no option to bail except to finish the trail, go back the way you came, or attempt to coordinate with your best friend to rescue you at Sunol, already twenty miles into the trail.</p><p>Additionally, Sunol was closed for a good share of 2023 due to the unusually rainy season. It's a better winter trail than a summer trail due to temperatures and sun exposure. And finally, it requires a <a href=\"https://www.ebparks.org/rentals-and-permits/permits/ohlone-wilderness\">trail permit</a> which although it only took five minutes to order—and is by a wide margin the nicest trail permit I've ever received—the small hurdle was enough to prevent an impulse decision once or twice.</p></div><div class=\"articleCards\"><div class=\"articleCards_marker\"><div class=\"articleCards_markerInner\"></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-metro articleCard-start\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"0\" style=\"min-height:0px\"><div class=\"articleCard_station\"><h2>Lake Merritt Station</h2></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-metro\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"0\" style=\"min-height:11750px\"><div class=\"articleCard_content\"><p>\n<img src=\"ohlone-wilderness-trail/ohlone-wilderness-trail-000-md-ed7a6ace.jpg\" alt=\"A BART station selfie\"></p><p>Despite previous experiences in which I <a href=\"trains-and-trails/mount-tam-golden-gate-loop/\">suggested I'd learned otherwise</a>, once the impulse decision had been made, I grabbed everything I thought I'd need, ran for the Lake Merritt BART Station without checking the schedule, and fortunately only had to wait about two minutes for the next train.</p></div><svg class=\"articleCard_circleCutoff\" width=\"20\" height=\"10\"><path d=\"M 0 0 L 20 0 L 20 10 A 14.5 14.5 0 0 0 0 10 Z\"></path></svg></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-metro articleCard-start\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"0.9975492343433984\" style=\"min-height:28px\"><div class=\"articleCard_station\"><h2>Dublin/Pleasanton Station</h2></div><svg class=\"articleCard_circleCutoff\" width=\"20\" height=\"10\"><path d=\"M 0 0 L 20 0 L 20 10 A 14.5 14.5 0 0 0 0 10 Z\"></path></svg></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-bus articleCard-start\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"1\" style=\"min-height:0px\"><div class=\"articleCard_station\"><h2>10R Bus to Livermore</h2></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-bus\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"1\" style=\"min-height:4299px\"><div class=\"articleCard_content\"><p>\n<img src=\"ohlone-wilderness-trail/ohlone-wilderness-trail-010-md-f9cd7abb.jpg\" alt=\"Waiting for the 10R\"></p><p>The twenty minute wait for the 10R bus to Livermore wasn't too bad, and there was even a bathroom at the station—which, when you're trying hard to overhydrate in preparation for a long day outside is no small amenity.</p></div><svg class=\"articleCard_circleCutoff\" width=\"20\" height=\"10\"><path d=\"M 0 0 L 20 0 L 20 10 A 14.5 14.5 0 0 0 0 10 Z\"></path></svg></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-foot articleCard-start\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"2\" style=\"min-height:0px\"><div class=\"articleCard_station\"><h2>Livermore</h2></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-foot\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"2\" style=\"min-height:1500px\"><div class=\"articleCard_content\"><p>\nI hopped off the bus at the point of closest approach to Lake Del Valle and began the day right at 10:00 AM. Given the scale of the day, it was, to say the least, an inadvisably late start.</p><p>I knew I'd be fine as long as I had my headlamp and enough water, but it was at this point I realized I'd forgotton my headlamp. I did the math and figured that at—worst case—45 miles at 5 miles per hour would put me at about a 7:00 PM finish, making a headlamp useful but not essential given I had my phone's flashlight and a backup battery.</p></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-foot\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"2.0333087737674225\" style=\"min-height:500px\"><div class=\"articleCard_content\"><p>\n<img src=\"ohlone-wilderness-trail/ohlone-wilderness-trail-020-md-a398728d.jpg\" alt=\"The bike path\"></p><p>The bike path was quite nice and allowed to skip running along any busy roads.</p></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-foot\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"2.0444116983565634\" style=\"min-height:2600px\"><div class=\"articleCard_content\"><p>\nSlightly nervous about running out of gas, I slammed the Gatorade I'd been carrying and stopped by a gas station for another Gatorade, a Clif Bar, and a bag of Lay's potato chips.</p></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-foot\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"2.1021469062200957\" style=\"min-height:1800px\"><div class=\"articleCard_content\"><p>\n<img src=\"ohlone-wilderness-trail/ohlone-wilderness-trail-030-md-a5a2fc44.jpg\" alt=\"The bike path\"></p><p>I was pleased to be running a steady pace on flat ground, although I knew it wouldn't last.</p></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-foot\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"2.142117434741003\" style=\"min-height:1200px\"><div class=\"articleCard_content\"><p>\n<img src=\"ohlone-wilderness-trail/ohlone-wilderness-trail-040-md-4a6ec4f7.jpg\" alt=\"The bike path\"></p><p>I knew the Ohlone trail would be easy to follow, but I was moderately worried about small wrong turns through local parks adding up to significant mileage. I had a bad feeling as I scrambled down a six foot vertical embankment to the brushy river bed below, but the trail got me where I needed to go.</p></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-foot\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"2.168764453754941\" style=\"min-height:500px\"><div class=\"articleCard_content\"><p>\n<img src=\"ohlone-wilderness-trail/ohlone-wilderness-trail-050-md-51c7a114.jpg\" alt=\"The bike path\"></p></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-foot\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"2.179867378344082\" style=\"min-height:2200px\"><div class=\"articleCard_content\"><p>\n<img src=\"ohlone-wilderness-trail/ohlone-wilderness-trail-060-md-dfd4ce25.jpg\" alt=\"The bike path\"></p></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-foot\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"2.2287202465363016\" style=\"min-height:1600px\"><div class=\"articleCard_content\"><p>\n<img src=\"ohlone-wilderness-trail/ohlone-wilderness-trail-070-md-d614d667.jpg\" alt=\"The bike path\"></p></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-foot\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"2.2642496052215524\" style=\"min-height:3200px\"><div class=\"articleCard_content\"><p>\n<img src=\"ohlone-wilderness-trail/ohlone-wilderness-trail-080-md-a93ba9db.jpg\" alt=\"The bike path\"></p></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-foot\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"2.335308322592054\" style=\"min-height:520px\"><div class=\"articleCard_content\"><p>\n<img src=\"ohlone-wilderness-trail/ohlone-wilderness-trail-090-md-3d63e9ca.jpg\" alt=\"The bike path\"></p></div><svg class=\"articleCard_circleCutoff\" width=\"20\" height=\"10\"><path d=\"M 0 0 L 20 0 L 20 10 A 14.5 14.5 0 0 0 0 10 Z\"></path></svg></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-foot articleCard-start\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"2.3468553641647603\" style=\"min-height:880px\"><div class=\"articleCard_station\"><h2>Ohlone Trailhead</h2></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-foot\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"2.366396511441648\" style=\"min-height:1950px\"><div class=\"articleCard_content\"><p>\n<img src=\"ohlone-wilderness-trail/ohlone-wilderness-trail-110-md-56ea2ced.jpg\" alt=\"The bike path\"></p></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-foot\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"2.4096979173392974\" style=\"min-height:4950px\"><div class=\"articleCard_content\"><p>\n<img src=\"ohlone-wilderness-trail/ohlone-wilderness-trail-120-md-d78a6b3e.jpg\" alt=\"The bike path\"></p></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-foot\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"2.519616870771792\" style=\"min-height:1900px\"><div class=\"articleCard_content\"><p>\n<img src=\"ohlone-wilderness-trail/ohlone-wilderness-trail-130-md-68572fbf.jpg\" alt=\"The bike path\"></p></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-foot\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"2.5618079842105272\" style=\"min-height:100px\"><div class=\"articleCard_content\"><p>\n<img src=\"ohlone-wilderness-trail/ohlone-wilderness-trail-140-md-2895b443.jpg\" alt=\"The bike path\"></p></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-foot\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"2.5640285691283555\" style=\"min-height:1500px\"><div class=\"articleCard_content\"><p>\n<img src=\"ohlone-wilderness-trail/ohlone-wilderness-trail-150-md-5acdff80.jpg\" alt=\"The bike path\"></p></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-foot\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"2.597337342895778\" style=\"min-height:700px\"><div class=\"articleCard_content\"><p>\n<img src=\"ohlone-wilderness-trail/ohlone-wilderness-trail-160-md-809cb990.jpg\" alt=\"The bike path\"></p></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-foot\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"2.612881437320575\" style=\"min-height:1600px\"><div class=\"articleCard_content\"><p>\n<img src=\"ohlone-wilderness-trail/ohlone-wilderness-trail-170-md-e7e539e5.jpg\" alt=\"The bike path\"></p></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-foot\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"2.648410796005826\" style=\"min-height:1300px\"><div class=\"articleCard_content\"><p>\n<img src=\"ohlone-wilderness-trail/ohlone-wilderness-trail-180-md-592b22c4.jpg\" alt=\"The bike path\"></p></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-foot\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"2.677278399937592\" style=\"min-height:2400px\"><div class=\"articleCard_content\"><p>\n<img src=\"ohlone-wilderness-trail/ohlone-wilderness-trail-190-md-dedb5463.jpg\" alt=\"The bike path\"></p></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-foot\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"2.7305724379654683\" style=\"min-height:12133px\"><div class=\"articleCard_content\"><p>\n<img src=\"ohlone-wilderness-trail/ohlone-wilderness-trail-200-md-64b025fd.jpg\" alt=\"The bike path\"></p></div></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-start articleCard-metro\" style=\"min-height:4500px\"></div><div class=\"articleCard articleCard-metro articleCard-terminus\" data-route-mode=\"follow\" data-route-progress=\"3.3237828053808487\" style=\"min-height:9398px\"><div class=\"articleCard_station\"><h2>12th Street Oakland</h2></div></div></div><div class=\"articleContent articleContent--conclusion\" data-route-mode=\"bound\"><p>I've not often been so satisfied with a run and so relieved to return home. My biggest regret was not putting on more sunscreen or perhaps bringing it with, though it did seem to have done its job, as I didn't end up with any discernible sunburn.</p><p><a href=\"\">Back</a></p></div>","metadata":{"title":"Ohlone Wilderness Trail","date":"December 23, 2023","assets":{"100":{"sm":"ohlone-wilderness-trail-100-sm-7185f89a.jpg","md":"ohlone-wilderness-trail-100-md-7185f89a.jpg","lg":"ohlone-wilderness-trail-100-lg-7185f89a.jpg"},"110":{"sm":"ohlone-wilderness-trail-110-sm-56ea2ced.jpg","md":"ohlone-wilderness-trail-110-md-56ea2ced.jpg","lg":"ohlone-wilderness-trail-110-lg-56ea2ced.jpg"},"120":{"sm":"ohlone-wilderness-trail-120-sm-d78a6b3e.jpg","md":"ohlone-wilderness-trail-120-md-d78a6b3e.jpg","lg":"ohlone-wilderness-trail-120-lg-d78a6b3e.jpg"},"130":{"sm":"ohlone-wilderness-trail-130-sm-68572fbf.jpg","md":"ohlone-wilderness-trail-130-md-68572fbf.jpg","lg":"ohlone-wilderness-trail-130-lg-68572fbf.jpg"},"140":{"sm":"ohlone-wilderness-trail-140-sm-2895b443.jpg","md":"ohlone-wilderness-trail-140-md-2895b443.jpg","lg":"ohlone-wilderness-trail-140-lg-2895b443.jpg"},"150":{"sm":"ohlone-wilderness-trail-150-sm-5acdff80.jpg","md":"ohlone-wilderness-trail-150-md-5acdff80.jpg","lg":